SIMPLE: domicillary
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Domicillary
<hw>Dom`i*cil"l*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>domiciliarius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a domicile, or
the residence of a person or family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The personal and <qex>domiciliary</qex> rights of the citizen
scrupulously guarded.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Domiciliary visit</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a visit
to a private dwelling, particularly for searching it, under
authority.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Domiciliate</ent>⟦br⟧
